td-ad5fd3: Sanitize reserved chain keys before checksum computation
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, security, code-quality

Description:
GA.Audit.create_log_entry/2 computes checksum from raw attrs before reserved chain fields are canonically enforced. Because normalize_attrs/1 keeps user keys and Chain.normalize_keys/1 stringifies keys, user-supplied "account_id" or "sequence_number" can collide with injected atom keys, producing an incorrect checksum for persisted rows. References: app/lib/app/audit.ex:21, app/lib/app/audit.ex:169, app/lib/app/audit/chain.ex:96.

Acceptance Criteria:
create_log_entry/2 ignores or rejects user-provided account_id/sequence_number/checksum keys (string and atom forms) before checksum generation; checksum is deterministic; a regression test proves verify_chain/1 stays valid when those keys are present in input attrs.

