td-c1fa7f: Avoid materializing huge missing-sequence lists in verifier
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P2
Labels: review-finding, performance, code-quality

Description:
GA.Audit.Verifier.verify_sequence/2 builds missing numbers with Enum.to_list(expected..(found - 1)). A malicious or corrupted jump in sequence_number can allocate an unbounded list and exhaust memory during verification. Reference: app/lib/app/audit/verifier.ex:72.

Acceptance Criteria:
Verifier reports sequence gaps without unbounded list allocation (for example by capping list size and tracking missing_count/range); large sequence jumps do not cause excessive memory growth; add tests for both small and very large gaps.

